docs.lead_paragraph: Most major pharmacies do not list the price of the drugs they sell, but two web companies are trying to make pricing information more transparent.

headline.main: New Online Tools Offer Path to Lower Drug Prices
headline.print_headline: Web Companies Are Pulling Back the Curtain on the Prices of Drugs

docs.abstract: GoodRx and Blink Health offer examples of companies that are trying to simplify annoyingly antiquated process of buying prescription drugs by using Internet; GoodRx seeks to connect consumers with coupons to help them save on drug prices, while Blink lets customers pay for drugs online, which they can then pick up at pharmacies.
docs.snippet: Most major pharmacies do not list the price of the drugs they sell, but two web companies are trying to make pricing information more transparent.
